{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-20T18:26:12.907Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prompt chaining patterns"},{"type":"text","text":" are the different architectural approaches you can use to structure sequential prompts. Each pattern solves a specific type of problem and has different trade-offs."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Linear Chain (Sequential Pipeline)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The most common pattern: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Step 1 → Step 2 → Step 3 →... → Final Output"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Prompt 1 → Output 1 → Prompt 2 → Output 2 → Prompt 3 → Output 3 → Final Result"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use case:"},{"type":"text","text":" Multi-step workflows where each step depends on the previous output"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example: Content Creation Pipeline"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 1: \"Research trending topics in SaaS for marketers\"\n→ Output: List of 5 trending topics\n\nStep 2: \"Based on these topics [Output 1], select the best one for a blog post\"\n→ Output: Selected topic + rationale\n\nStep 3: \"Using this topic [Output 2], write a blog post outline with 5 sections\"\n→ Output: Detailed outline\n\nStep 4: \"Based on this outline [Output 3], write the full blog post\"\n→ Output: Complete blog post"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Clear, predictable flow\n- Easy to debug at each step\n- Good for content pipelines"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Limitations:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Can't handle parallel tasks\n- Sequential (slower)"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Branching Chain (Parallel Processing)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Multiple parallel chains that "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"merge"},{"type":"text","text":" at the end:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Prompt 1 → Output 1 → Prompt 2A → Output 2A\n                     ↘\n                      Prompt 3 → Final Result\n                     ↗\nPrompt 1 → Output 1 → Prompt 2B → Output 2B"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use case:"},{"type":"text","text":" When you need to process multiple aspects independently then combine"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example: Multi-Perspective Analysis"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 1: \"Analyze this product from a technical perspective\"\n→ Output: Technical analysis\n\nStep 2A: \"Analyze this product from a business perspective [Output 1]\"\n→ Output: Business analysis\n\nStep 2B: \"Analyze this product from a user experience perspective [Output 1]\"\n→ Output: UX analysis\n\nStep 3: \"Combine these analyses [Output 2A + Output 2B] into a comprehensive review\"\n→ Output: Final review"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Faster (parallel processing)\n- Captures multiple perspectives\n- Better for complex analysis"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Limitations:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- More complex to manage\n- Requires merging logic"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Recursive Chain (Iterative Refinement)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The output loops back to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"improve itself"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Prompt 1 → Output 1 → Prompt 2 (improve Output 1) → Output 2 → Prompt 3 (improve Output 2) → Final Output"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use case:"},{"type":"text","text":" Iterative refinement, quality improvement"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example: Code Refinement Loop"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 1: \"Write a Python function to calculate factorial\"\n→ Output: Initial implementation\n\nStep 2: \"Review this code [Output 1] for security vulnerabilities\"\n→ Output: Security analysis\n\nStep 3: \"Fix any security issues identified [Output 2] in this code [Output 1]\"\n→ Output: Fixed implementation\n\nStep 4: \"Review the fixed code [Output 3] and suggest performance improvements\"\n→ Output: Performance suggestions\n\nStep 5: \"Apply these performance improvements [Output 4] to the code [Output 3]\"\n→ Output: Final optimized code"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Improves quality iteratively\n- Catches issues early\n- Good for code, writing"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Limitations:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Can loop too many times\n- Computationally expensive"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Conditional Chain (Decision Tree)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The chain "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"branches based on intermediate outputs"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Prompt 1 → Output 1 → IF condition A → Chain A\n                     IF condition B → Chain B\n                     IF condition C → Chain C"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use case:"},{"type":"text","text":" Decision-making, customer support"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example: Customer Support Triage"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 1: \"What type of issue are you experiencing?\"\n→ Output: User selects \" billing\"\n\nStep 2 (IF billing): \"How much were you charged?\"\n→ Output: \"$50\"\n\nStep 3 (IF billing): \"This appears to be a billing error. Here's how to resolve it...\"\n→ Output: Resolution\n\n---\n\nStep 2 (IF technical): \"What error message are you seeing?\"\n→ Output: \"Error 404\"\n\nStep 3 (IF technical): \"Let's debug this. First, check your browser...\"\n→ Output: Troubleshooting steps"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Handles different scenarios\n- Personalized responses\n- Good for support"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Limitations:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Complex branching logic\n- Many possible paths"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"5. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Aggregating Chain (Multi-Source Synthesis)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Multiple inputs "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"combine into one output"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Source A → Prompt A → Output A\nSource B → Prompt B → Output B  → Prompt Final → Final Output\nSource C → Prompt C → Output C"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use case:"},{"type":"text","text":" Research synthesis, comparing sources"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example: Research Paper Review"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Paper A: \"Summarize the key findings from this research paper\"\n→ Output: Summary A\n\nPaper B: \"Summarize the key findings from this research paper\"\n→ Output: Summary B\n\nPaper C: \"Summarize the key findings from this research paper\"\n→ Output: Summary C\n\nFinal: \"Compare these summaries [Output A + Output B + Output C] and synthesize common themes\"\n→ Output: Comprehensive review"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Synthesizes multiple sources\n- Captures diverse perspectives\n- Good for research"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Limitations:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Require source management\n- Complex aggregation logic"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"6. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Feedback Loop Chain (Human-in-the-Loop)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Involves "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"human review"},{"type":"text","text":" at intermediate steps:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Prompt 1 → Output 1 → Human Review → IF approved → Prompt 2\n                                   IF rejected → Modify Output 1"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use case:"},{"type":"text","text":" Quality control, regulated content"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example: Legal Document Review"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 1: \"Draft a contract clause for [topic]\"\n→ Output: Initial clause\n\nStep 2: \"Review this clause [Output 1] for legal compliance\"\n→ Output: Compliance analysis\n\nStep 3: [Human reviews compliance analysis]\n→ Decision: \"Approved\" or \"Needs revision\"\n\nStep 4 (IF approved): \"Finalize this clause [Output 1] with the approved language\"\n→ Output: Final clause\n\nStep 4 (IF rejected): \"Revise this clause [Output 1] based on these concerns [Human feedback]\"\n→ Output: Revised clause"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Human oversight\n- Quality control\n- Regulatory compliance"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Limitations:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Slower (requires human)\n- More complex workflow"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"7. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Decomposition Chain (Task Breaking)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Break a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"single complex task"},{"type":"text","text":" into subtasks:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Complex Task → Break into Subtasks → Subtask 1 → Subtask 2 → Subtask 3 → Combine → Final Output"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use case:"},{"type":"text","text":" Complex problem-solving, research"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example: Business Strategy Development"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Original Task: \"Develop a comprehensive business strategy for our SaaS company\"\n\nBreak into:\n1. Market analysis\n2. Target audience research\n3. Competitive positioning\n4. Revenue model\n5. Go-to-market strategy\n\nSubtask 1: \"Analyze the current market trends for SaaS\"\n→ Output: Market analysis\n\nSubtask 2: \"Research the target audience for SaaS products\"\n→ Output: Audience research\n\nSubtask 3: \"Identify key competitors and their positioning\"\n→ Output: Competitive analysis\n\nSubtask 4: \"Design a revenue model based on market and audience data [Output 1 + Output 2]\"\n→ Output: Revenue model\n\nSubtask 5: \"Create a go-to-market strategy using all previous analysis [Output 1-4]\"\n→ Output: GTM strategy\n\nFinal: \"Combine all subtasks into a comprehensive business strategy document\"\n→ Output: Final strategy"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Handles very complex tasks\n- Clear structure\n- Good for strategy"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Limitations:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Many steps\n- Requires careful planning"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Pattern Comparison Table"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Pattern"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Structure"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Best For"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Complexity"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Speed"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Linear"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"SequentialPipeline"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Content, workflows"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Low"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Medium"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Branching"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Parallel→Merge"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Multi-perspective analysis"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Medium"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fast"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Recursive"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Loop→Improve"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Code, writing refinement"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"High"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Slow"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Conditional"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Decision Tree"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Support, triage"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Medium"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fast"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Aggregating"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Multi-Source→Combine"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Research synthesis"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Medium"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Medium"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Feedback Loop"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Human Review"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Quality control"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"High"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Slow"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Decomposition"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Break→Subtasks→Combine"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Complex problems"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"High"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Medium"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Best Practices for Chaining Patterns"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Start Simple (Linear)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"For beginners: Start with Chain-of-Thought (CoT) or Decomposition for tasks requiring structured reasoning without advanced tool integration."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Begin with linear chains, then add complexity as needed."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Pass Context Between Steps"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"In prompt chaining, chain prompts perform transformations or additional processes on the generated responses before reaching a final desired state."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Always pass the previous output to the next prompt with clear context."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 2: \"Based on this analysis [Output 1], create...\""}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use Clear Delimiters"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"It helps if you design two different prompts where the first prompt is responsible for extracting relevant quotes to answer a question and a second prompt takes as input the quotes and original document to answer a given question."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use XML tags or clear formatting to separate outputs."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Output 1: <summary>Text here</summary>\nOutput 2: <plan>Based on <summary>...</summary>, the plan is...</plan>"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Design for Debugging"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Besides achieving better performance, prompt chaining helps to boost the transparency of your LLM application, increases controllability, and reliability. This means that you can debug problems with model responses much more easily and analyze and improve performance in the different stages that need improvement."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Each step should be independently testable."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"5. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Limit Chain Length"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Long chains can accumulate errors. Keep chains to 3-5 steps unless necessary."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"6. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Handle Failures Gracefully"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For conditional and branching chains, design fallback paths for when conditions aren met."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Summary"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Seven chaining patterns:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Linear Chain"},{"type":"text","text":" — Sequential pipeline (Step 1 → Step 2 → Step 3)"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- Best for: Content, workflows - Complexity: Low | Speed: Medium"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Branching Chain"},{"type":"text","text":" — Parallel processing then merge"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- Best for: Multi-perspective analysis - Complexity: Medium | Speed: Fast"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Recursive Chain"},{"type":"text","text":" — Loop to improve iteratively"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- Best for: Code, writing refinement - Complexity: High | Speed: Slow"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Conditional Chain"},{"type":"text","text":" — Decision tree based on outputs"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- Best for: Support, triage - Complexity: Medium | Speed: Fast"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Aggregating Chain"},{"type":"text","text":" — Multi-source synthesis"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- Best for: Research synthesis - Complexity: Medium | Speed: Medium"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Feedback Loop Chain"},{"type":"text","text":" — Human-in-the-loop"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- Best for: Quality control - Complexity: High | Speed: Slow"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Decomposition Chain"},{"type":"text","text":" — Break complex task into subtasks"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- Best for: Complex problems - Complexity: High | Speed: Medium"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Best practices:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Start simple"},{"type":"text","text":" — Begin with linear chains\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Pass context"},{"type":"text","text":" — Always pass previous output\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use delimiters"},{"type":"text","text":" — XML tags for clarity\n4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Design for debugging"},{"type":"text","text":" — Independent testability\n5. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Limit chain length"},{"type":"text","text":" — 3-5 steps typically\n6. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Handle failures"},{"type":"text","text":" — Fallback paths"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prompt chaining is useful to accomplish complex tasks which an LLM might struggle to address if prompted with a very detailed prompt."}]}]}}
